-- Bayer May Invest to Make Kogenate at Wuppertal Plant, FTD Says
-- B y   J a n a   R a n d o w
-- 2012-07-29T20:46:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-29/bayer-may-invest-to-make-kogenate-at-wuppertal-plant-ftd-says.html
Bayer AG (BAYN)  may invest in its Wuppertal
plant to produce the drug Kogenate  Financial Times Deutschland 
reported, citing unidentified people within the company.  Bayer is considering remodeling a plant formerly used to
produce the drug Trasylol, and plans to spend about 80 million
euros ($99 million), according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
 jrandow@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  